9 FLOOR SUBSTITUTE
10 An Act relating to Medicaid home- and community-based
services; amending 10 O.S. 2021, Section 1408, which
11 relates to definitions; modifying certain definition;
updating statutory language and references; and
12 providing an effective date.
13
14
15 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
16 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY 10 O.S. 2021, Section 1408, is
17 amended to read as follows:
18 Section 1408. A. “Individual with intellectual disability” as
19 used in Sections Section 1406 through 1424 et seq. of this title
20 means a person who has significantly subaverage functioning,
21 intelligence quotient of less than seventy (70), manifested before
22 the age of eighteen (18) and existing concurrently with related
23 limitations in two or more of the following applicable adaptive
24 skill areas:
Req. No. 3796 Page 1

1 1. Communication;
2 2. Self-care;
3 3. Home living;
4 4. Social skills;
5 5. Use of community resources;
6 6. Self-direction;
7 7. Health and safety;
8 8. Functional academics;
9 9. Leisure; and
10 10. Work meets the criteria for intellectual disorder as listed
11 in the Social Security Administration Listing of Impairments for
12 disability evaluation, 20 C.F.R., Part 404, Subpart P.
13 B. “Resident” as used in Sections Section 1406 through 1424 et
14 seq. of this title shall mean a person admitted to and in residence
15 in any of the institutions named in Section 1406 of this title, or
16 on a vacation or extended vacation status from such institution.
17 C. “Developmental disability” as used in Sections Section 1406
18 through 1424 et seq. of this title means a severe, chronic
19 disability of a person which:
20 1. Is attributable to a mental or physical impairment or
21 combination of mental and physical impairments, such as intellectual
22 developmental disorder, cerebral palsy, or autism;
23 2. Is manifested before the person attains twenty-two (22)
24 years of age;
Req. No. 3796 Page 2

1 3. Is likely to continue indefinitely;
2 4. Results in substantial functional limitations in three or
3 more of the following areas of major life activity:
4 a. self-care,
5 b. receptive and expressive language,
6 c. learning,
7 d. mobility,
8 e. self-direction,
9 f. capacity for independent living, and
10 g. economic self-sufficiency; and
11 5. Reflects the person’s need for a combination and sequence of
12 special, interdisciplinary, or generic care, treatment, or other
13 services which are of lifelong or extended duration and are
14 individually planned and coordinated. The term developmental
15 disability shall not include mentally ill incompetent persons, as
16 those persons are defined by Section 1-103 of Title 43A of the
17 Oklahoma Statutes, whose sole disability is mental illness as
18 defined by Section 1-103 of Title 43A of the Oklahoma Statutes.
19 D. Nothing in subsection C of this section shall be construed
20 to render persons who are receiving services upon September 1, 1991,
21 through programs and services for individuals with intellectual
22 disabilities offered by the Department of Human Services as
23 ineligible for such services. The Department of Human Services may
24 provide, within the limitations of funds and other resources
Req. No. 3796 Page 3

1 avai lable for such purpose, programs and services for persons with
2 developmental disabilities who are not presently served by the
3 Department of Human Services.
4 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective November 1, 2026.
